2.20	Hugo_de_Groot	Hugo Grotius	Hugo Grotius (10 April 1583 â€“ 28 August 1645), also known as Huig de Groot, Hugo Grocio or Hugo de Groot, was a jurist in the Dutch Republic. With Francisco de Vitoria and Alberico Gentili he laid the foundations for international law, based on natural law. He was also a philosopher, theologian, Christian apologist, playwright, and poet.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/80/Michiel_Jansz_van_Mierevelt_-_Hugo_Grotius.jpg/220px-Michiel_Jansz_van_Mierevelt_-_Hugo_Grotius.jpg
